               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-317-person2662">
                  CHARLES 
                  HIPKINS
               <interp inst="t18300415-317-person2662" type="surname" value="HIPKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-317-person2662" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-317-person2662" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw the prosesecutor on the 25th of March, who said he had lost his clothes - I went to Brunswick-place, Commercial-road, with him; he asked if the prisoner was at home - his mother said No; he asked to see his bag, and these things were turned out of it - I went in search of the <rs id="t18300415-317-deflabel1735" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-317-defend2659 t18300415-317-deflabel1735"></join>, and found him; I asked what he had done with the waistcoat, if he had pawned it - he said No - I took him to the station, and asked him again - then he said he had pawned it for 1s.; I went to the pawnbroker's, and found it, with this half handkerchief, which the prosecutor said had been in one when he had it - the prisoner then said he took it from the ship; the prosecutor is now gone to sea, but he saw the property and swore to it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-317-person2663">
                  CHARLES 
                  WILLIAMSON
               <interp inst="t18300415-317-person2663" type="surname" value="WILLIAMSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-317-person2663" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-317-person2663" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. On the 25th of March the prisoner pawned this waistcoat with me; the prosecutor saw it, and swore to it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The comb that was found in my bag I had had three or four months - I bought it myself; the sailor said it was his.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 14.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300415-317-verdict1736" type="verdictDescription">
